{
  "stem": "11801.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He lived with one family for many years and then lived with different families in that village until the late '50s or early '60s, when his behavior changed.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He became violent.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He became-- he started breaking windows or smashing furniture.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I'm not quite sure.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I never got all the details.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And for maybe a few months, he was placed in a psychiatric institution.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In that same village, they had a psychiatric institution.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I remember, we visited him there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "This was, of course, long after the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "My late husband and I visited him there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] eventually he was sent to Saint Truiden.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Saint-- Saint Truiden, T-R-U-I-D-E-N, which is another small village in Belgium, which has a very large psychiatric institution.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And here to this day, he's there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "He's been there all his life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I mean, he's been in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Belgians have taken care of him lovingly and beautifully all of his life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "It's incredible.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They have never asked for a penny.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "In fact, when my mother passed away, I had made sure that she left him some money.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I didn't think it was fair that, you know, because he was handicapped, that he'd be left out of her will.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we took the money over there, and my husband and I, on our yearly visit.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we told them that this was not really for him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He doesn't need anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "He's not-- he doesn't-- you know, things mean nothing to him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "He doesn't want a radio.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "He doesn't want a watch.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "He got-- he has all the clothes he needs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "He has pocket money, but he doesn't need anything else.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
